<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:s="https://admin.wvusports.com/services/xml_schema/story" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"><channel><title>West Virginia University Athletics</title><link>https://admin.wvusports.com/rss.aspx</link><description>Latest news items for West Virginia University Athletics</description><atom:link href="https://admin.wvusports.com/rss" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><language>en-us</language><ttl>60</ttl><item><title>West Virginia Concludes Road Trip With Win at Arizona</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/1/baseball-west-virginia-concludes-road-trip-with-win-at-arizona</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/1/baseball-west-virginia-concludes-road-trip-with-win-at-arizona</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Carson Estridge" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/31/EKQ08234.jpeg" /><br /><br />TUCSON, Ariz. – The No. 13 West Virginia University baseball team defeated Arizona, 7-4, Tuesday night in a non-conference game at Hi Corbett Field. The Mountaineers improve to 20-5 while the Wildcats fall to 9-19.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/31/EKQ08234.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/31/EKQ08234.jpeg"><media:title>Carson Estridge</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/31/EKQ08234.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 1 Apr 2026 02:08:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58944</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia Set to Play at Arizona</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/30/baseball-west-virginia-set-to-play-at-arizona</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/30/baseball-west-virginia-set-to-play-at-arizona</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Matchup at Arizona" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/30/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Arizona.jpg" /><br /><br />PHOENIX – The No. 13 West Virginia University baseball team caps off its trip to the Valley of the Sun with a midweek non-conference game on March 31, against Arizona. First pitch from Hi Corbett Field in Tucson is set for 9 p.m. ET.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/30/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Arizona.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/30/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Arizona.jpg"><media:title>Matchup at Arizona</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/30/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Arizona.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 30 Mar 2026 17:48:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58942</s:story_id></item><item><title>McDonald Named Student-Athlete of the Week</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/30/track-field-mcdonald-named-student-athlete-of-the-week</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/30/track-field-mcdonald-named-student-athlete-of-the-week</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Annishka McDonald @ Raliegh Relays" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/30/IMG_3142.jpeg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Redshirt junior Annishka McDonald of the West Virginia University track and field team has been named the WVU Student-Athlete of the Week, presented by University Apartments.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/30/IMG_3142.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/30/IMG_3142.jpeg"><media:title>Annishka McDonald @ Raliegh Relays</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/30/IMG_3142.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 30 Mar 2026 11:05:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>16</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58941</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Claim Series From No. 22 Arizona State</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/30/baseball-mountaineers-claim-series-from-no-22-arizona-state</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/30/baseball-mountaineers-claim-series-from-no-22-arizona-state</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Chansen Cole, Gavin Kelly" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/29/EKQ07574.jpeg" /><br /><br />PHOENIX – The No. 17 West Virginia University baseball team earned a ranked Big 12 series win on Sunday night with a 9-5 victory over No. 22 Arizona State in front on a national TV audience. The Mountaineers improve to 19-5 and 7-2 in the Big 12 while the Sun Devils fall to 20-8 and 5-4 in conference play.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/29/EKQ07574.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/29/EKQ07574.jpeg"><media:title>Chansen Cole, Gavin Kelly</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/29/EKQ07574.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 30 Mar 2026 00:50:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58940</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Even Series Against No. 22 Arizona State</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/29/baseball-mountaineers-even-series-against-no-22-arizona-state</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/29/baseball-mountaineers-even-series-against-no-22-arizona-state</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Maxx Yehl" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/28/EKQ07337.jpeg" /><br /><br />PHOENIX – The No. 17 West Virginia University baseball team defeated No. 22 Arizona State, 13-7, Saturday night at Phoenix Municipal Stadium to even up the series at a game apiece. The Mountaineers improve to 18-5 overall and 6-2 in the Big 12 while the Sun Devils fall to 20-7 and 5-3 in league play.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/28/EKQ07337.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/28/EKQ07337.jpeg"><media:title>Maxx Yehl</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/28/EKQ07337.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 29 Mar 2026 02:28:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58939</s:story_id></item><item><title>McDonald Sets Outdoor School Record at Raleigh Relays</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/28/track-field-mcdonald-sets-outdoor-school-record-at-raleigh-relays</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/28/track-field-mcdonald-sets-outdoor-school-record-at-raleigh-relays</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Annishka McDonald" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/1/29/annishkahighjump.png" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Annishka McDonald highlighted West Virginia's weekend at the Raleigh Relays, setting a new outdoor school record in the high jump.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/1/29/annishkahighjump.png" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/1/29/annishkahighjump.png"><media:title>Annishka McDonald</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/1/29/annishkahighjump.png" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 28 Mar 2026 22:06:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>16</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58938</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Sweep Cincinnati for First Conference Victory</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/28/tennis-mountaineers-sweep-cincinnati-for-first-conference-victory</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/28/tennis-mountaineers-sweep-cincinnati-for-first-conference-victory</guid><category>Tennis</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Tennis Team" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/28/BBD01669.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University tennis team (7-9, 1-8 Big 12) earned its first conference win of the season on Saturday morning, defeating Cincinnati (6-10, 1-8 Big 12), 4-0, at the Summit 